stateDiagram-v2
[*] --> flow_registered
state "flow_registered<br/>Flow detail recorded in flowsRunning (type and optional amount) via startFlow()." as flow_registered
flow_registered --> planned: Steps were provided inline (offerArgs.flow) so execution can start without planner.
flow_registered --> planning: No steps provided, planner must compute and resolve flow(n).steps.
state "planning<br/>Planner computes steps/order from balances + targetAllocation and posts flow(n).steps." as planning
planning --> planned: flow(n).steps published (and optional order) by planner.
planning --> failed: Planner/solver errored or allocation infeasible.
state "planned<br/>Concrete MovementDesc[] (and optional deterministic order) available at flow(n).steps." as planned
planned --> executing: executePlan() begins, FlowStatus state=run emitted.
planned --> planning: policyVersion incremented or targetAllocation changed before execution.
state "executing<br/>Contract performing ordered movements, publishes FlowStatus run/fail/done." as executing {
  [*] --> provisioning
  state "provisioning<br/>Make/resolve accounts (Agoric, Noble, EVM) and register resolver pending transactions when needed." as provisioning
  provisioning --> moving: provideCosmosAccount/provideEVMAccount resolved, accountsPending empty.
  provisioning --> failed: Account creation or resolver registerTransaction failed.
  state "moving<br/>Execute MovementDesc steps (localTransfer, withdrawToSeat, send, IBC, CCTP, GMP, protocol supply/withdraw). FlowStatus state=run advances, fail publishes FlowStatus state=fail. IBC legs can block if relayer is down/slow." as moving {
    [*] --> dispatch
    state "dispatch<br/>Performing the current movement. For IBC legs, once packet is sent funds are escrowed at source until relay." as dispatch
    dispatch --> ibc_wait_relayer: IBC transfer enqueued, funds escrowed on source chain.
    dispatch --> dispatch: IBC ack received and step finished, proceed to next movement.
    state "ibc_wait_relayer<br/>Waiting on relayer to deliver packet to destination chain, funds escrowed at source." as ibc_wait_relayer
    ibc_wait_relayer --> ibc_wait_ack: Destination chain processed packet (recv/ack pending).
    ibc_wait_relayer --> ibc_timeout_refund: Packet timed out, refund path should unescrow.
    state "ibc_wait_ack<br/>Packet received and funds credited at destination, waiting for ack to be written on source." as ibc_wait_ack
    ibc_wait_ack --> dispatch: Ack observed, IBC leg complete.
    ibc_wait_ack --> ibc_timeout_refund: Timeout observed instead of ack, refund path should unescrow.
    state "ibc_timeout_refund<br/>Timeout detected, funds should be refunded/unescrowed on source chain. If refund fails, operator action required." as ibc_timeout_refund
    ibc_timeout_refund --> dispatch: Refund confirmed, resume execution with remaining steps.
    ibc_timeout_refund --> failed: Refund did not post, funds stuck in escrow.
  }
  moving --> failed: FlowStatus state=fail emitted for a step.
  moving --> settling: Tx requiring confirmation added to pendingTxs (MAKE_ACCOUNT, GMP, CCTP out/in).
  moving --> completed: FlowStatus state=done and no TxStatus pending.
  state "settling<br/>Waiting on cross-chain confirmations from resolver (TxStatus pending -> success/failed)." as settling
  settling --> moving: All pendingTxs for this flow settled success, continue or finish.
  settling --> failed: pendingTx updated to failed.
}
executing --> failed: FlowStatus state=fail emitted.
executing --> completed: FlowStatus state=done and all relevant pendingTxs are success.
state "completed<br/>Flow finished, balances/positions updated, pendingTxs (if any) marked success." as completed
completed --> [*]
state "failed<br/>Flow halted, partial effects possible, operator or planner must retry/correct." as failed
failed --> [*]
